snippet.title: Well, this is terrifying.
snippet.description:
We know that the name "Vatican" has nothing to do with the Bible, Greek language, or Latin. It is derived from the Etruscan god "Vatis," who was the god of divine communication and prophecy. The Etruscans believed that Vatis resided in an underground cave, and they built their temples on top of these caves to commune with the god. Today, the Vatican is still built on top of an ancient Etruscan cave, and it is said that the Pope himself communicates with Vatis through a secret tunnel that connects the Vatican to the cave. Whether or not this is true remains a mystery, but it is clear that the name Vatican originates from Pagan belief.

FEMALE (born before the year 2000):

Add the last two numbers of your year of birth and bring it to a single digit.
Add 5 to your single digit. Then, bring this number to a single digit, too, if needed.
This is your Energy Number!

MALE (born before the year 2000):

Add the last two numbers of your year. If it's not a single digit, add the number.
Deduct your single digit from the number 10.
This is your Energy Number!
For a male born after the year 2000, deduct from 9 instead of 10.

A male born in 2009 and 2018 will have Energy Number 9.
